OL,6,FSeamus Dooley, the Irish Secretary of
OL,7,Fthe National Union of Journalists,
OL,8,Fsaid Mr Bird's life "should not be
OL,9,Fdefined by his illness".
OL,11,FHe said: "Supported by his wife
OL,12,FClaire, Charlie lived his battle with
OL,13,FMotor Neurone Disease in the public
OL,14,Fgaze, with characteristic
OL,15,Fdetermination and searing honesty.
OL,17,F"The qualities he has manifested
OL,18,Fduring his illness ` grit, fierce
OL,19,Fdetermination and generosity of
OL,20,Fspirit, were the same qualities which
OL,21,Fmarked Charlie Bird as a journalist."
